ions, and morality. The book provides insights for scholars in phenomenological philosophy as well as in philosophy of mind and interpersonal and social experience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEmpathyxPhilosophy. 0aPhenomenology. 0aPhilosophyxSocial aspects. 4aEmpathie. 4aGefühle. 4aIntersubjektivität. 4aPhänomenologie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aPhenomenology.  aemotions.  aempathy.  aintersubjectivity.1 aBortolan, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBortolan, Anna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCrowell, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrummond, John J, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFussi, Alessandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeinämaa, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHopkins, Burt C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInverso, Hernán G, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeane, Niall, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLau, Kwok-ying, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Nam-In, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoidolt, Sophie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagrì, Elisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagrì, Elisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMoran, Dermot, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurchadha, Felix Ó, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNenon, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id